.SH NAME
EXT_texture_compression_bptc \- EXT_texture_compression_bptc extension
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]EXT_texture_compression_bptc\f[R] extension is part of the
WebGL API and exposes 4 BPTC compressed texture formats.
These compression formats are called \c
.UR https://docs.microsoft.com/windows/win32/direct3d11/bc7-format
BC7
.UE \c
\ and \c
.UR https://docs.microsoft.com/windows/win32/direct3d11/bc6h-format
BC6H
.UE \c
\ in \c
.UR https://docs.microsoft.com/windows/win32/direct3d11/texture-block-compression-in-direct3d-11
Microsoft\[cq]s DirectX API
.UE \c
\&.
.PP
WebGL extensions are available using the
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.getExtension()\f[R] method.
For more information, see also Using Extensions in the WebGL tutorial.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Support depends on the system\[cq]s graphics driver.
There is no support on Windows.
.PP
This extension is available to both, WebGL1 and WebGL2 contexts.
.RE
.SH CONSTANTS
The compressed texture formats are exposed by 4 constants and can be
used in two functions: \f[CR]compressedTexImage2D()\f[R] and
\f[CR]compressedTexSubImage2D()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGBA_BPTC_UNORM_EXT\f[R]
Compresses 8\-bit fixed\-point data.
Each 4x4 block of texels consists of 128 bits of RGBA or image data.
See also \c
.UR https://docs.microsoft.com/windows/win32/direct3d11/bc7-format
BC7 format
.UE \c
\&.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_BPTC_UNORM_EXT\f[R]
Compresses 8\-bit fixed\-point data.
Each 4x4 block of texels consists of 128 bits of SRGB_ALPHA or image
data.
See also \c
.UR https://docs.microsoft.com/windows/win32/direct3d11/bc7-format
BC7 format
.UE \c
\&.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_SIGNED_FLOAT_EXT\f[R]
Compresses high dynamic range signed floating point values.
Each 4x4 block of texels consists of 128 bits of RGB data.
It only contains RGB data, so the returned alpha value is 1.0.
See also \c
.UR https://docs.microsoft.com/windows/win32/direct3d11/bc6h-format
BC6H format
.UE \c
\&.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_UNSIGNED_FLOAT_EXT\f[R]
Compresses high dynamic range unsigned floating point values.
Each 4x4 block of texels consists of 128 bits of RGB data.
It only contains RGB data, so the returned alpha value is 1.0.
See also \c
.UR https://docs.microsoft.com/windows/win32/direct3d11/bc6h-format
BC6H format
.UE \c
\&.
